  "texts": [
    "For most MRS time-domain stellar objects, the Hα profiles of multiple observations are consistent as the example shown in Figure 1.",
    "A few stellar sources do show discrepancies between the Hα profiles of multiple observations, which might be owing to the observation or calibration issues.",
    "In the line wings, the discrepancy is mainly manifested as the offset of the normalized spectral fluxes (see example diagram in Appendix C.1); and in the line center, the discrepancy is mainly manifested as the distortion of the spectral profiles (see example diagram in Appendix C.2).",
    "In order to recognize the objects with consistent Hα profiles in the line wings, for each stellar source, we first sort the Hα spectra of multiple observations by their I Hα index values (reflecting mean normalized flux at line center; see definition in Section 4.1), and calculate the means of the normalized fluxes in two line-wing bands on the violet and red sides of the Hα line for each of the spectra.",
    "The central wavelengths of the two line-wing bands are ±4.5 Å from the Hα line center, and the widths of the two line-wing bands are both 2 Å (see illustration in Appendix C.1)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}